Author: D2D privacyalternatives.com#5667
Content:
I had asked for opinions about a VPN (Lethean) on this thread a day ago, but didn't get any feedback.
I also asked a friend and this is what he said :
"I don't trust the dVPN that asked for a listing. They have a weak white paper that is short on technicals, and very little explanations about how exit nodes (the people selling their bandiwdth for coins) would protect themselves against illegal activities by end users"
So I decided to don't list it on the directory

Author: gcharang#6833
Content:
their tech might be solid
"threshold signatures"
but their advertising is misleading
they say 'keyless', but what they mean is, they integrated icloud with their app as a backup solution for the user's half of the private key
so the user won't lose coins even if they lose the device
